    public class ObjectList<Element>
extends BaseList<Element>
    A bounded list of objects with overrides of methods from BaseList to downcast return values to ObjectList for convenience. New instances of ObjectList are created by BaseList by calling onNewInstance(), allowing functional logic to reside in the base class.

    Partitioning

    • partition(Count) - The elements in this list partitioned into N new lists

    The methods objectList(Object[]) and objectList(Maximum, Object[]) can be used to construct constant lists. The factory methods objectListFromInts(IntMapFactory, int...) and objectListFromLongs(LongMapFactory, long...) construct lists of objects from integer and long values using the given map factories to convert the values into objects. The method objectList(Iterable, LongMapFactory) iterates through the given Quantizable values, passing each quantum to the given primitive map factory and adding the resulting object to a new object list.
